    "headline": "Resmed Chief Financial Officer Brett Sandercock to Retire; Aaron Bloomer Appointed as Successor",
    "summary": "SAN DIEGO, April 30, 2026 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Resmed (NYSE: RMD, ASX: RMD), the leading health technology company focused on sleep, breathing and care delivered in the home, today announced that Brett Sandercock, Chief Financial Officer, plans to retire effective May 4, 2026. After conducting a comprehensive search, Aaron Bloomer has been appointed as his successor. “After 27 years with Resmed, including 20 as CFO, Brett leaves an outstanding legacy of disciplined leadership and trusted partners",
